parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or slow down, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions or other accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or slows down without warning
often with no obstacles or vehicles in front of it; the brake warning light or "BRAKE" message appears on the dashboard; the vehicle may stop or slow down abruptly
even when there is no apparent reason to do so.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to unexpected braking, loss of power, and other safety issues, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences unexpected braking
loss of power
warning lights on the dashboard
and strange noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, accidents, and distractions while driving, which can lead to serious consequences.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
chemical smoke is present in the vehicle
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden and unexpected braking
brake warning lights on the dashboard
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ANC system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Loud buzzing or humming noise is present in the vehicle
and the noise is random and frequent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle experiences loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's sudden and unexpected braking can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle brakes suddenly without warning
even when there are no obstacles or vehicles in front of it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud humming noise caused by the ANC system failure can be a distraction while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: A loud humming noise is produced
which can be intermittent or constant
and can be loud enough to be a distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Blind spots can cause accidents, and malfunctioning windows can be a safety hazard, especially during emergency situations.
symptoms: Blind spots in the vehicle
passenger window not rolling down
or stuck in the up position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and shifting issues can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle becomes stuck in gear or fails to shift properly.
symptoms: The vehicle's transmission gets stuck in park
or the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system and component failures can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if they affect critical safety systems.
symptoms: Various electrical system and component failures
including issues with the brake system
parking brake
and ANC system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The traffic sign recognition system error can cause driver confusion, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The system misrecognizes speed limit signs
leading to incorrect speed limit displays.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unusual noises and vibrations can be a distraction while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Various unusual noises and vibrations
including loud humming
rattling
or droning sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
warped rotors
shaking or vibrating when braking
excessive brake dust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted automatic braking engagements can cause sudden stops, increase the risk of rear-end collisions, and lead to accidents.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected braking
emergency braking warning signal on the dash
autonomous braking without obstacles or vehicles in front.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear brake issues can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Screeching or grinding noise from the rear brakes
warped rear rotors
excessive wear on rear brake pads
shaking or vibrating when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and brake pedal issues can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
delayed return of the clutch pedal.
